cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning (DRL) and proposes a novel method to handle combinatorial actions in a card game. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves game theory and adversarial training, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible sub-category. The authors use a two-stage network and max-pooling operations, indicating that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) could also be relevant sub-categories.
